com.here.android.mpa.mapping

Class MapContainer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.here.android.mpa.common.ViewObject
      • com.here.android.mpa.mapping.MapObject
        • com.here.android.mpa.mapping.MapContainer

  • public final class MapContainer
extends MapObject
    Represents a container that determines the stacking order of objects on a Map. Applications can add certain types of MapObject objects into a MapContainer. For more details, refer to MapContainer.addMapObject(MapObject).

    • Method Detail

      • addMapObject

        public boolean addMapObject(MapObject object)
        Adds a MapObject to this MapContainer. Types of MapObject objects that can be added include:
        • MapMarker objects
        • MapLabeledMarker objects
        • MapScreenMarker objects
        • MapCircle objects
        • MapPolyline objects
        • MapPolygon objects
        • MapContainer objects (Note: not supported as of Release 2.0)

        For a complete enumeration of available MapObject types, refer to MapObject.Type.

        Parameters:
        object - A MapObject to add to this MapContainer
        Returns:
        True if the MapObject was added successfully to this MapContainer, false otherwise
        See Also:
        MapContainer.removeMapObject(MapObject)

      • removeMapObject

        public boolean removeMapObject(MapObject object)
        Removes the specified MapObject from this MapContainer. If the specified MapObject is not contained within the MapContainer, the container will be unchanged.
        Parameters:
        object - A MapObject to remove from this MapContainer
        Returns:
        True if the MapObject was removed successfully from this MapContainer , false otherwise
        See Also:
        MapContainer.removeAllMapObjects()

      • removeAllMapObjects

        public boolean removeAllMapObjects()
        Removes all MapObject objects currently within this MapContainer.
        Returns:
        True if all MapObject objects were removed successfully from this MapContainer, false otherwise
        See Also:
        MapContainer.removeMapObject(MapObject)

      • getAllMapObjects

        public java.util.List<MapObject> getAllMapObjects()
        Returns the list of all MapObject objects within this MapContainer. Modifications to objects returned from the array are not guaranteed to be reflected properly in the MapContainer. Use MapContainer.addMapObject(MapObject) and MapContainer.removeMapObject(MapObject) to modify individual array elements.

        Note: the order of the MapObjects returned in the List is arbitrary. There is no guarantee the list is sorted in the order the MapObjects were added to the MapContainer.

        Returns:
        A list containing all MapObject objects within the MapContainer. If the MapContainer contains no map object, an empty array will be returned.
